G8b36Z1VqmBtd4JfcRqOE7WWEQVPBAUEzX9Fh74NxN7mEjsD1OUphUDpgax6AvG9tnzr6aNG3CZ_MYL-OF0H4hLkCfwhEFStnmBm32BC3VUazAXoCHv-beSdZ0dK-Uio3LrcJ-218QRxMDX4-z9rMmxCwbyBh6jRPew5xKxxAwngVfQcpkrXVpP2eQ8I20CcAotlILEIVuYeNeZLRXFLNSvzC8AS_yV9AK_pxjPobQg14-HD7flDs4oLrwSd13i745tTG7vXz1I0ZfJ_j98s2WAez6UeZxoQKyVTGaGZ7IuTrCSfvwNvTlNhQ0zg==\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering compilation and testing**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm thinking about the process here: the infrastructure likely runs the agent before compiling native code. Since there's an existing build with generated configs from a previous test, I don’t need to do it manually — that's a relief! I just need to ensure that the Java compile is public at the top level. Should I handle deprecated warnings? The compile seems okay. I’ll also want to make sure that test methods can combine all call sites, especially for dynamic coverage, which needs to execute each line.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Considering package references**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm thinking about referencing `Instantiable.class` in my tests and possibly using reflection. It seems necessary to check if I need the package outside of the library, specifically `org_keycloak.keycloak_client_common_synced`. I'm wondering if I even have to use direct reflection for this task, or if there's a more straightforward approach. It’s good to assess all the paths available before making a final decision.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"toolCall\\\", \\\"id\\\": \\\"call_9r6z5csCJUulhC8OtG3vhNmY|fc_05479656d881c4b80169f6dae1649481a1865e9ad09ee4951f\\\", \\\"name\\\": \\\"write\\\", \\\"arguments\\\": {\\\"path\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/ReflectionsTest.java\\\", \\\"content\\\": \\\"/*\\\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\\\n *\\\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\\\n */\\\\npackage org_keycloak.keycloak_client_common_synced;\\\\n\\\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\\\n\\\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Constructor;\\\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\\\\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\\\\nimport java.util.Arrays;\\\\nimport java.util.List;\\\\nimport java.util.Set;\\\\n\\\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\\\nimport org.keycloak.common.util.reflections.Reflections;\\\\n\\\\npublic class ReflectionsTest {\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void shouldLoadClassesWithContextBootstrapAndAdditionalClassLoaders() throws Exception {\\\\n        ClassLoader originalClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\\\\n        try {\\\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(ReflectionsTest.class.getClassLoader());\\\\n            assertThat(Reflections.classForName(String.class.getName())).isSameAs(String.class);\\\\n\\\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(null);\\\\n            assertThat(Reflections.classForName(Integer.class.getName())).isSameAs(Integer.class);\\\\n\\\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(new RejectingClassLoader());\\\\n            assertThat(Reflections.classForName(Long.class.getName(), Long.class.getClassLoader())).isSameAs(Long.class);\\\\n        } finally {\\\\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(originalClassLoader);\\\\n        }\\\\n    }\\\\n\\\\n    @Test\\\\n    void shouldInspectDeclaredMembersAcrossClassHierarchy() {\\\\n        Set<Field> fields = Reflections.getAllDeclaredFields(ReflectionSubject.class);\\\\n        assertThat(fields).extracting(Field::getName).contains(\\\\\\\"parentValue\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"publicValue\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"rawItems\\\\\\\");\\\\n\\\\n        Field parentValue = Reflections.findDeclaredField(ReflectionSub